(this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]=this["webpackJsonppersonal-site"]||[]).push([[7],{161:function(e,n,t){"use strict";t.r(n);var i=t(53),a=(t(1),t(5)),o=t(62),r=t.n(o),s=t(21),c=t(0),h="\r\n# Intro\r\n\r\nI am a Senior at Virginia Tech majoring in Computer Engineer with a focus in Machine Learning and minoring in Computer Science. I am interested in learning and applying both Software Development and Machine Learning, specifically Deep Learning and Reinforcement Learning to solve challenging problems. I used my toolbox of programming, machine learning, and mathematics to solve these problems. I am also gaining intested in Controls Theory, its applications toward Robotics, and its combination with Reinforcement Learning. Besides, I am passionate about technology applying in both commercials and the Department of Defense (DoD). If you think I can be helpful to you/your team/your company or would like to meet me (both in person or virtually), feel free to get in touch.\r\n\r\n# Background\r\nI was born in the beautiful [Ho Chi Minh City](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ilui-mb3sT0&ab_channel=BeautifulDestinations), Viet Nam. I moved to the United State when I was 18 years old and have been living in the State ever since.\r\n\r\n# Research Interests\r\nCan be found in [here](https://mnguyen0226.github.io/personal-site/stats).\r\n\r\n# Current Work\r\n\r\nThis Summer 2021, I am currently interning with Heron Systems R&D as Machine Learning Intern and working on [Game Breaker](https://heronsystems.com/work/gamebreaker/) project funded by Defense Advanced Reseasrch Projects Agency (DARPA) in which I apply technical skills such as Python/Pytorch best-practice, Deep Learning, and Reinforcement Learning techniques in exploring new capabilities, tactics, and rule modifications that are most destabilizing to the game. This project provides a great benchmark for the DoD's long-term development of Battle Management Systems (BMS).<br><br>\r\nBesides, I am also participating in the \"Model Specific Assurance\" of Virginia Tech's [A3 Lab](https://ai.ece.vt.edu/) where I built a pipeline in Pytorch for Deep Learning's Explainabilty AI (XAI) and Security AI for image classification. My work is part of the \"Model Specific-Model Agnostic Assurance\".<br><br>\r\n*I shared these two sections below because my friends mentioned my site was just my resume. I hope this small section of my personal interest and journey somewhat make it more interesting and can connect with you in some extend :)*\r\n# Personal Interests\r\n- Self-learning and building things with software.\r\n- Chess.\r\n- [Chinese Chess](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xiangqi) (Xiangqi).\r\n- Stand-up comedy, dad jokes, and [good memes](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ&ab_channel=RickAstley).\r\n- Sports: running, soccer, hiking, competitive frisbee, wally/volley-ball.\r\n- Long-boarding.\r\n- Skiing.\r\n- Dark coffee / Expresso.\r\n- Classical Piano, American Pop, UK Rap.\r\n- Current top-3 cooking dishes I can make: Thai Curry, KFC Fry Chicken, Vietnamese Beef Rattles.\r\n- Current top-3 audio books: Art of Wars, The Killing Chain, 48 Laws of Power.\r\n- Current top-3 Spotify podcasts: [Lex Fridman](https://open.spotify.com/show/2MAi0BvDc6GTFvKFPXnkCL), [The Economist](https://www.economist.com/podcasts), [The Minimalist](https://open.spotify.com/show/5ECF0soZ1H5NxZHanAzUYd).\r\n\r\n# Travel Journey\r\n- I have spend 4/5 of my life in the the beautiful Ho Chi Minh City, Viet Nam. I have traveled through ~30/63 provinces of Viet Nam, some of which I have forgotten, and many of which I would like to revisit due to the weather, people, good foods, and diverst cultures. I planned to travel Europe in my late 20s. One of my long-term goals is to travel through all 50 states in the US.\r\n- In 2014, I visited Seoul (South Korea).\r\n- In 2015, I moved to St.Paul-Minneapolis Twin City (Minnesota, USA). Besides, I visited Wisconsin and  Virginia.\r\n- In 2017, I visited Singapore and Washington DC (USA)\r\n- In 2018, I moved to Blacksburg (Virginia, USA). Here, I hiked in Cascade Falls, Dragon's Tooth Hike, McAfee Knob.\r\n- In 2019, I visited Greesboro (North Carolina, USA), Myrtle Beach (South Carolina, USA), New York City/Albany/Buffalo (New York, USA), Philadelphia (Pennsylvania, USA), Boston (Massachusetts, USA).\r\n- In 2021, I am a Washington DC's museums enthusiast.",l=h.split(/\s+/).map((function(e){return e.replace(/\W/g,"")})).filter((function(e){return e.length})).length,d=function(e){var n=Object.assign({},e);return Object(c.jsx)(a.b,Object(i.a)({},n))};n.default=function(){return Object(c.jsx)(s.a,{title:"About",description:"Learn about Minh T. Nguyen",children:Object(c.jsxs)("article",{className:"post markdown",id:"about",children:[Object(c.jsx)("header",{children:Object(c.jsxs)("div",{className:"title",children:[Object(c.jsx)("h2",{"data-testid":"heading",children:Object(c.jsx)(a.b,{to:"/about",children:"About Me"})}),Object(c.jsxs)("p",{children:["(in about ",l," words)"]})]})}),Object(c.jsx)(r.a,{source:h,renderers:{Link:d},escapeHtml:!1})]})})}}}]);
